com.microsoft.band

Enum BandErrorType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<BandErrorType>
      • com.microsoft.band.BandErrorType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<BandErrorType>

    public enum BandErrorType
extends java.lang.Enum<BandErrorType>
    Enumeration of error types

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      BAND_FULL_ERROR
      A value representing an error from trying to add a tile to an already full Microsoft Band
      DEVICE_ERROR
      A value representing an error in communication with the Microsoft Band over bluetooth (Usually means the Microsoft Band is out of range or that bluetooth is turned off)
      INVALID_LAYOUT_ERROR
      A value representing an error from trying to add a tile with an invalid layout
      INVALID_LAYOUT_INDEX_ERROR
      A value representing an error from trying to send data to an undefined layout
      INVALID_PAGE_DATA_ERROR
      A value representing an error from trying to send too much data to a single page on a tile
      MULTIPLE_LONG_STRING_ERROR
      A value representing an error from trying to send multiple strings with more than 20 characters to a single page on a tile
      PERMISSION_ERROR
      A value representing an error resulting from attempting to access protected information
      SERVICE_ERROR
      A value representing an error in communication with Microsoft Health's band communication service (A common cause is Microsoft Health not being installed)
      TILE_ALREADY_EXISTS_ERROR
      A value representing an error from trying to add a tile to a Microsoft Band that already has a tile with the same UUID
      TILE_ID_IN_USE_ERROR
      A value representing an error from trying to add a tile with the tileId that is already used by other application
      TILE_NOT_FOUND_ERROR
      A value representing an error from trying to send data to a tile that does not exist
      TIMEOUT_ERROR
      A value representing an error resulting from communication with Microsoft Health's band communication service timing out
      TOO_MANY_CONCURRENT_COMMANDS_ERROR
      A value representing an error from trying to send too many simultaneous commands to Microsoft Health's band communication service
      UNKNOWN_ERROR
      A value representing an error due to an unknown origin
      UNSUPPORTED_SDK_VERSION_ERROR
      A value representing an error resulting from a mismatch in version between the SDK and Microsoft Health
